I'm building on OS X Tiger, using the "vecLib" framework implementation of
LAPACK, so results may differ across platforms. Otherwise using libc, fftw3 (not 2),
and a static library compiled from the modified SNAPHU sources.

This is my compilation command:

gcc -g -o auto_shim auto_shim.c data.c image.c -framework vecLib -I/opt/local/include -L./punwrap -L/opt/local/lib -lm -lfftw3 -lunwrap

I don't know how many extra linking calls you need on Linux for clapack.

to compile libunwrap.a :

cd punwrap/
gcc -g -c cfile.c -O (for all cfiles)
ar -rv libunwrap.a obj1.o obj2.o obj3.o .... (for all objects)
ranlib libunwrap.a
